commit.message: Update poetry.lock
Clean up and organize .gitignore
Update all target to update, regenerate, test, and build everything
Add check target to Makefile to run all checks

Add typecheck target to Makefile

Currently it will run `mypy`.

Add 'venv' and 'update' targets to Makefile

'venv' will explicitly create a local venv with poetry, 'update' will
update all dependencies in poetry.lock and .pre-commit-config.yaml.
Amend Makefile to allow for not having a global 'poetry' install
Add mypy configuration to pyproject.toml
Add mypy, pre-commit, and tox to dev-dependencies

Add 'help' target to Makefile

It will read the Makefile itself to emit comments starting with '## '
as documentation for each target.  It's a bit fragile, but allows for
multiple lines of help for a target.

Inspired by, and some doc strings taken from, Nate's work in #196.

Co-Authored-By: Nate Schimmoller <nate.schimmoller@klaviyo.com>
Remove redundant arguments from CI test command

Skip test_has_version_attribute outside installation

It's not really supported configuration, but a skip is friendlier than
an error.

Fixes #108.
